@startuml
' Purpose: Score alias mapping into policy evaluation scope
' Source of truth:
'   src/api/service/journeyResolver.ts
'   src/api/service/policy.ts

title Score Aliasing - Scope Mapping Sequence Diagram

actor System
participant "JourneyTemplateEntry" as Entry
participant "Service" as Service
participant "PolicyScope" as Scope

System -> Entry : Read scoreAliases\n{ "OSS.total": "scores.ossTotal",\n  "pain.avg": "scores.painAverage" }
Service -> Service : Read latest FormResponse.scores
Service -> Scope : Build base scope\nfrom raw score keys
Service -> Scope : Inject aliases from JourneyTemplateEntry\n(scoreAliases + scoreAliasLabels)
Scope --> Service : Final numeric scope\n{ scores.ossTotal: 22,\n  OSS.total: 22,\n  pain.avg: 7.5 }
Service -> PolicyParser : evaluateExpression(rule, finalScope)

note right
  Aliasing is computed in:
  src/api/service/journeyResolver.ts
  buildPolicyScopeWithAliases(...)

  Benefit:
  Policy authors can write stable,
  clinically meaningful identifiers
  independent of raw scoring key names.
end note

@enduml
